Package soot.rtlib.tamiflex Description

This package contains classes that may be emitted into a program during code generation. If Soot cannot find a class on the soot-classpath then it automatically loads the class from Soot's own JAR file but only if this class is in this package. This is to avoid accidental mix-ups between the classes of the application being analyzed and Soot's own classes. To add a class, use, for example, the following: 

 //before calling soot.Main.main
 Scene.v().addBasicClass(SootSig.class.getName(),SootClass.BODIES);
 
 //then at some point
 Scene.v().getSootClass(SootSig.class.getName()).setApplicationClass();
This will cause Soot to emit the class SootSig along with the analyzed program.
